    <text id="B0546T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>How responds to an enquiry from the Quartermaster Department related to his
                    service before becoming Superintendent of the 6th District.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Brevet Brigadier General">Bt. Brig.
                        Gen.</abbr> Geo. R. Rutherford<lb/>Office of the <abbr
                            expan="Quartermaster General">QM Genl</abbr> of the Army<lb/>Washington,
                        D.C.<lb/>Washington, D.C.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-11-24"><abbr expan="November">Nov</abbr> 24th 1865</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <abbr expan="General">Genl</abbr>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I am this day in receipt of your letter in relation to <abbr expan="General"
                    >Gen</abbr> orders No. 51 Current Series which order I have not as yet received
                    or read.</p>

                <p>On the 30th day of September 1865 I had no Employees serving under me in the
                        <abbr expan="Quartermaster Department">QM Dept</abbr> because I was then, as
                    now on duty in the Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands, as
                    Superintendent of the Sixth District <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> and since
                    the 1st of October 1863, I have neither employed Printers for a compensation nor
                    paid any person for such services.</p>

                <p>My Post Office address as previously reported by me to the Quarter Master General
                    is <hi rend="underline">Winchester</hi>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>, and the direction of your communication to
                    Staunton is the reason of this delay in replying to it.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am General &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>W Storer How<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp;c</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
